qas.question: How close to the ground was the Lunar Module in May 1969 during its landing test?
The Lunar Module completed its first low Earth orbit on what date?

context: The American Lunar Module was finally ready for a successful piloted test flight in low Earth orbit on Apollo 9 in <a1_0>March 1969<a1_0/>. The next mission, Apollo 10, conducted a "dress rehearsal" for the first landing in May 1969, flying the LM in lunar orbit as close as <a0_0>47,400 feet<a0_0/> (14.4 km) above the surface, the point where the powered descent to the surface would begin. With the LM proven to work well, the next step was to attempt the actual landing.
